  "title": "QUALITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p>· Report to the Project Director.</p>\n<p>· Overall in charge of site coordination.</p>\n<p>· Lead a team of operation staff in daily operations.</p>\n<p>· Manage and oversee the day-to-day construction activities of the project.</p>\n<p>· Monitor and control the general workers' deployment on-site.</p>\n<p>· Maintain and manage site storage areas for building materials and equipment.</p>\n<p>· Maintain site access throughout the construction period.</p>\n<p>· Planning ahead to prevent the problem on-site before it occurs, planning the delivery and storage of equipment and materials.</p>\n<p>· Ensure progress of work is within budget and timelines as well as quality and safety objectives.</p>\n<p>· Control and monitor work progress and resources.</p>\n<p>· Monitor and control material wastage.</p>\n<p>· In-depth understanding of project specifications, technical details, and construction drawings.</p>\n<p>· Carry out work scheduling, material requisition planning, project coordination, and documentation.</p>\n<p>· Ensure timely completion and good quality of works &amp; carried out safely and WSHE regulations are complied with.</p>\n<p>· Provide proper guidance and training to junior staff.</p>\n<p>· Other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the Immediate Supervisor/ Management.</p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirement:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proven experience as Site Manager</li>\n  <li>In-depth understanding of construction procedures and material and project management principles</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with quality and health and safety standards</li>\n  <li>Outstanding communications and negotiation skills</li>\n  <li>Excellent organizational and time-management skills</li>\n  <li>A team player with leadership abilities</li>\n  <li>Advances time management and analytical skills</li>\n  <li>Excellent client-facing communication skills</li>\n  <li>Candidate must pass at least Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent. Diploma holders or equivalent with relevant experience BSc/BA in Engineering (Civil) or Engineering (Metal Fabrication/Tool &amp; Die/Welding) or relevant field <strong>(Degree is recognized by BCA will be an advantage)</strong></li>\n  <li>5 years' experience in Site Management <strong>(Metal Works)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>· Required language(s): English &amp; Mandarin (in order to handle queries and feedbacks from English &amp; Mandarin speaking associates, clients and customers)</p>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
